comments: Markkanen (UTA) brings his hands forward and marginal contact occurs with Jackson (IND) after the pick is set.
Nesmith (IND) and Olynyk (UTA) mutually engage in pursuit of the rebound and marginal contact occurs.
As both players reach for the ball, Olynyk (UTA) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds and IND should retain possession.
The ball is last touched by Hield (IND) before going out of bounds and UTA should retain possession.
Nesmith (IND) establishes himself in Agbaji's (UTA) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Haliburton (IND) legally contests Clarkson's (UTA) jump shot attempt.

Hield (IND) grazes Clarkson's (UTA) face as he swings the ball to his other side and the contact is marginal.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Haliburton's (IND) jump shot bounces over the backboard and goes out of bounds.
Sexton (UTA) and Mathurin (IND) make incidental foot to foot during the inbound pass.
Haliburton (IND) commits a take foul on Clarkson (UTA).
Haliburton (IND) initiates contact with Markkanen's (UTA) arm during the drive and affects his SQBR.
Nesmith (IND) deflects the ball out of bounds.
Nesmith (IND) commits a take foul on Markkanen (UTA).
Agbaji (UTA) brings his arm slightly forward and marginal contact occurs with Mathurin's (IND) arm during his driving shot attempt.
